// docs/spec/en/05-unions-and-packed-layout.md §9.4(2)'s note lists an
// id-expression naming a `constexpr` variable as an accepted bound form,
// with no requirement that the constant live at global scope. A *local*
// `constexpr` constant, declared earlier in the same function, is just as
// usable as a later local array's bound as a *global* `constexpr`
// constant already is (see the sibling
// array_bound_literal_sizeof_alignof_arithmetic_and_named_constant_are_accepted.scpp
// case) -- the early, non-executing pass that resolves array bounds ahead
// of ordinary statement execution binds each local `constexpr`
// declaration into its own constant-evaluation frame stack as it walks a
// function body in order, exactly mirroring how that same pass already
// makes local `constexpr` values available as `alignas` operands within
// the same function.
int main() {
    constexpr int kLocalSize = 4;
    char buf[kLocalSize];
    buf[0] = 'a';
    return 0;
}
